<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900801-0052</DOCNO><DOCID>900801-0052.</DOCID><HL>   International Brief -- Petrofina S.A..   Petrochemical Concern's Net   Fell 12% for 1990 First Half</HL><DATE>08/01/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   B.PET</CO><IN>EARNINGS (ERN)</IN><LP>   Petrofina S.A. said lower petrochemical prices and theweak dollar knocked its net profit down 12% in the firsthalf.   The Belgian oil and petrochemical company said net profittotaled 10.13 billion Belgian francs ($306.8 million), downfrom 11.49 billion Belgian francs a year earlier. The companydidn't provide figures for total sales.</LP><TEXT>   On the Brussels Bourse, Petrofina shares slipped 225Belgian francs to close at 11,800 Belgian francs. Patrick deBellefroid, chief analyst at Puissant Baeyens Poswick andamp; Cie.,called the results &quot;a bit disappointing&quot; and said his firmmight have to reduce its forecast for the full year, whichhad called for earnings about even with 1989's 21.82 billionBelgian francs.   Though Petrofina's petrochemical results were downsubstantially in the half, the company said profit marginsbegan to improve in the second quarter for two of its mainproducts, high-density polyethylene and polypropylene.   The weak dollar hurt Petrofina's results partly becausethe company derives substantial income from its AmericanPetrofina Inc. unit.   In Europe, Petrofina said its sales of gasoline and othermotor fuels rose 8%.</TEXT></DOC>